[Question]
Write a simple website in HTML. When a user clicks the button, it shows a random joke from a list of 4 jokes.

[The Start of Reference Answer]
Certainly! Below is a simple example of an HTML document that includes a bit of JavaScript to display a random joke from a list of four jokes when a user clicks a button. This example is basic and intended to demonstrate the concept. You might want to expand or modify it for more complex applications.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
    <script>
        // Function to display a random joke
        function showRandomJoke() {
            // Array of jokes
            var jokes = [
                "Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything.",
                "Why did the chicken go to the séance? To talk to the other side.",
                "I told my wife she should embrace her mistakes. She gave me a hug.",
                "Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts."
            ];

            // Generate a random index based on the number of jokes
            var randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);

            // Display the joke at the random index
            document.getElementById("jokeDisplay").innerHTML = jokes[randomIndex];
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Random Joke Generator</h2>
<button onclick="showRandomJoke()">Tell me a joke</button>
<p id="jokeDisplay"></p> <!-- Placeholder for the joke -->

</body>
</html>
```

### How It Works:

1. **HTML Structure**: The HTML sets up a simple page with a title, a button, and a paragraph (`<p>`) element where the joke will be displayed.

2. **JavaScript Function (`showRandomJoke`)**: This function is triggered when the user clicks the button. It selects a random joke from the `jokes` array and displays it by setting the `innerHTML` of the paragraph with the id `jokeDisplay`.

3. **Event Listener**: The `onclick` attribute on the button calls the `showRandomJoke` function when clicked.

Feel free to customize the jokes or the overall design to better fit your needs!
[The End of Reference Answer]

